<subSubSection id="0EF06ADEFFB18805AE141DEDFBA6B70B" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="46553955FFB18805AE141DEDFBA6B70B" blockId="9.[264,1325,284,1241]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="749EE547FFB18805AE141DEDFE64B722" box="[312,414,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Remarks</emphasis>
. This is the most yellow species of 
<taxonomicName id="81EA42D6FFB18805AC711DEDFC64B722" box="[861,926,1015,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Pieza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="749EE547FFB18805AC711DEDFC64B722" box="[861,926,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Pieza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
known. Some specimens appear orange, but this is probably due to a hypercyanic condition after capture.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0EF06ADEFFB18805AE141A5DFE70B783" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="46553955FFB18805AE141A5DFE70B783" blockId="9.[264,1325,284,1241]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="749EE547FFB18805AE141A5DFE49B752" box="[312,435,1095,1120]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet derives from the Latin “ 
<emphasis id="749EE547FFB18805ACC51A5DFBFFB752" box="[1001,1029,1095,1120]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">de</emphasis>
” = away from, down + “ 
<emphasis id="749EE547FFB18805AE391A75FE80B7BA" box="[277,378,1135,1160]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">resistens</emphasis>
” = firm, tough; referring to the relative fragility of the only known four female specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0EF06ADEFFB18805AE141AA5FB90B7EB" box="[312,1130,1215,1241]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="distribution">
